  <div class="block-3">
    <div class="inner-block" id="responsibilities">
      <section class="responsibilities_for_ministerial_role responsibilities" id="responsibilities_for_ministerial_role_2679">
        <h1>Responsibilities</h1>
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>The Parliamentary Under Secretary of State will support the work of the Department for Exiting the European Union.</p>

<ul>
  <li>Policy Coordination & Delivery</li>
  <li>Contingency Planning</li>
  <li>International Agreements and trade</li>
  <li>Borders</li>
  <li>Secondary legislation</li>
  <li>EU (Withdrawal Agreement) Bill support</li>
</ul>
</div>
</section>
        <section class="current-role-holder" id="current-role-holder">
          <h1>Current role holder: <span class="name">James Cleverly MP</span>
</h1>
          <div class="govspeak">
<p>James Cleverly MP was appointed as a Parliamentary Under Secretary of State at the Department for Exiting the European Union on 4 April 2019.</p>
</div>
          <div class="read-more">
            <a href="/government/people/james-cleverly">More about this person</a>
          </div>
        </section>

